'''Dragon Warrior''' (known as '''Dragon Quest''' in Japan) is a role-playing video game developed by Chunsoft and published by Enix for the Nintendo Entertainment System. It is the first game in the Dragon Quest series and one of the most influential JRPGs ever made.

==Overview==

Dragon Warrior established many conventions of the JRPG genre, including random enemy encounters, a turn-based battle system, and character progression through experience points and levels.

